&lt;p&gt;The Account Manager is responsible for driving revenue growth for synthetic biology and life science reagent products in Korea. This role is highly customer-facing and requires frequent engagement with academic researchers, biotech companies, and pharmaceutical organizations.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The primary focus of this position is field-based sales activities, including customer meetings, scientific discussions, opportunity development, and relationship management. The Account Manager will work closely with internal technical teams and channel partners to deliver a strong customer experience and expand business opportunities in the Korean market.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;div&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/div&gt;
&lt;div&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Key Responsibilities&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/div&gt;
&lt;h2&gt;Customer-Facing Sales Activities&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Spend the majority of time on customer-facing sales activities, including in-person meetings, lab visits, and scientific discussions with researchers.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Build and maintain strong relationships with principal investigators (PI), researchers, and R&amp;amp;D leaders in academia, biotech, and pharmaceutical companies.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Identify customer needs and propose appropriate solutions using synthetic biology products and services.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Manage customer interactions across the full sales cycle, including opportunity development, quotation, order follow-up, and post-sales support.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;h2&gt;Revenue Growth &amp;amp; Territory Management&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Achieve assigned quarterly and annual revenue targets.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Develop and execute territory plans to expand business in the Korean market.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Maintain a healthy sales pipeline and deliver accurate sales forecasts.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Identify and develop new business opportunities within existing and new accounts.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Monitor market trends and competitor activities within the synthetic biology and life science research markets.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Provide market insights and customer feedback to internal teams.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Support the introduction of new products and solutions based on customer needs.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;h2&gt;Collaboration &amp;amp; Internal Coordination&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Work closely with technical support teams (FAS / application scientists) to support customer discussions when needed.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Collaborate with operations and internal teams to ensure smooth order processing and customer satisfaction.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Maintain accurate records of customer interactions and opportunities in CRM systems.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Represent the company at scientific conferences, academic meetings, and industry events.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Support local marketing activities, including seminars, workshops, and customer engagement programs.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;h1&gt;Qualifications&lt;/h1&gt;
&lt;h2&gt;Experience&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Minimum 2–5 years of experience in life science sales, preferably in reagents, genomics, or synthetic biology products.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Experience selling to academic institutions, biotech companies, or pharmaceutical organizations in Korea.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Experience in customer-facing field sales roles is strongly preferred.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;h2&gt;Technical Background&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Basic understanding of molecular biology, genomics, or synthetic biology workflows.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Ability to communicate scientific concepts effectiv

&lt;p&gt;We are seeking a passionate, highly skilled, and results-driven leader to build and scale Twist Bioscience’s global logistics function. The Director of Logistics is responsible for overseeing all aspects of shipping, logistics, and warehousing operations — including cold chain management and international distribution — ensuring that our Next Gen Sequencing and&amp;nbsp; DNA Synthesis products reach customers worldwide safely, compliantly, and on time. This senior leadership role requires deep expertise in biotech supply chains, cross-border regulatory requirements, and temperature-controlled logistics to support Twist’s rapid growth and mission to transform life sciences.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;What You’ll Be Doing &lt;/strong&gt;[Essential Duties/Responsibilities]&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Lead and develop Twist’s end-to-end logistics organization, including domestic and international shipping, warehousing, and cold chain operations, building a high-performing team aligned to company growth objectives.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Continuously improve cold chain logistics programs to ensure product integrity throughout storage, handling, and transportation through the supply base to customers.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Oversee international shipping operations including customs clearance, import/export compliance, Incoterms selection, and coordination with freight forwarders, brokers, and carriers across all major global trade lanes.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Manage warehouse operations across all Twist’s facilities, ensuring best-in-class inventory accuracy, space utilization, safety compliance, and order fulfillment performance for both commercial and R&amp;amp;D product lines.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Develop and manage relationships with couriers, cold chain logistics vendors, and freight forwarders; lead RFP/RFQ processes and negotiate contracts to optimize service levels and costs.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Partner with Supply Chain, Manufacturing, Quality, R&amp;amp;D, Finance, and Customer Support teams to align logistics operations with production schedules, customer commitments, and cost targets.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Define and track key logistics KPIs and present regular performance reporting to senior leadership.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Develop scalable logistics infrastructure to support Twist’s global expansion, including evaluation of regional distribution strategies, warehouse network optimization, and new market entry logistics planning.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Follow regulatory and ISO 13485.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;What You’ll Bring to the Team &lt;/strong&gt;[Competency/Qualifications]&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Bachelor’s degree in Supply Chain Management, Logistics, Business, Engineering, or a related field required; advanced degree (MBA or MS) preferred.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;12+ years of progressive logistics and supply chain experience, with at least 5 years in a senior leadership role managing multi-site or global logistics operations in a life sciences, biotech, or pharmaceutical company.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Deep expertise in cold chain logistics, including validated temperature-controlled transport (2–8°C, –20°C, –80°C/dry ice), and packaging qualification.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Proven track record in international shipping and trade compliance.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Strong warehousing and 3PL management experience, including WMS implementation and optimization, inventory control processes, and regulatory compliance.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Demonstrated ability to manage and develop high-performing teams across multiple locations; a collaborative, servant-leadership style with the energy to inspire and hold teams accountable in a fast-paced environment.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Hands-on experience with ERP/TMS/WMS systems (SAP preferred) for logistics management, as well as data analytics tools.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Excellent financial acumen with the ability to develop and manage a logist

&lt;h2&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Equipment Engineer (onsite in South San Francisco, CA )&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;h3&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Job Description&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The Equipment Engineer is responsible for ensuring the reliability and performance of all production instrumentation within a high-throughput DNA synthesis environment. You will be the primary lead for validating equipment, performing routine and preventative maintenance, and executing complex troubleshooting to minimize downtime.The ideal candidate is a self-motivated problem-solver who thrives in a fast-paced setting and is committed to maintaining the rigorous quality metrics required for cutting-edge biotechnology production.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;h3&gt;&lt;strong&gt;What You’ll Be Doing&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Equipment Validation: Lead the execution of Installation Qualification (IQ), Operational Qualification (OQ), and Performance Qualification (PQ) for both new and existing instrumentation.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Preventative Maintenance: Manage the scheduling and execution of routine maintenance and calibrations in strict accordance with manufacturer specifications and internal quality standards.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Troubleshooting: Investigate recurring equipment failures to implement permanent engineering fixes, significantly reducing or eliminating downtime.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Quality Compliance: Own and ensure the timely closure of equipment-related CAPAs (Corrective and Preventive Actions) and Change Controls.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Inventory &amp;amp; Logistics: Instrument, spare part, and service purchasing, from order submission to receipt of goods.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Cross-Functional Collaboration: Partner closely with Process Engineers to understand equipment-process interactions and ensure hardware operates within peak specifications.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;h3&gt;&lt;strong&gt;What You’ll Bring to the Team&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Education: BS in Engineering, Physical Sciences, or a related technical discipline.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Experience: Minimum of 1-3 years of professional experience in equipment maintenance, calibration, and repair.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Technical Versatility: Proven ability to design and build projects to improve reliability using mechanical, electrical, and electro-mechanical systems&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Quality Mindset: High attention to detail and strong organizational skills; experience working under ISO 9001, ISO 13485, or GMP/cGMP standards is highly preferred.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Adaptability: Ability to multi-task in a dynamic environment and work comfortably in a cleanroom setting (requiring lab coats, hairnets, and gloves).&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Good computer skills (Excel, Word, Atlassian etc) and the ability to quickly learn new software applications.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Communication: Excellent interpersonal skills with a collaborative approach to problem-solving.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Strong documentation experience, drafting technical documentation, and managing maintenance records.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Bonus Assets: Experience with automated liquid handlers, robotics, or MES/LIMS integration is a significant plus.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;h2&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 400;&quot;&gt;About Twist Bioscience&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 400;&quot;&gt;Twist Bioscience synthesizes genes from scratch, known as “writing” DNA. Just as children learn to both read and write, the next phase of development for the genomics revolution is the ability to write DNA.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 400;&quot;&gt;At Twist Bioscience, we work in service of people who are changing the world for the better. In fields such as health care, agriculture, industrial chemicals and data storage, our unique silicon-based DNA Synthesis Platform provides precision at a scale that is otherwise un

&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;职位概述&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;该职位需要一位兼具深厚技术背景与出色沟通能力的专家。您将成为连接公司产品与客户成功之间的关键桥梁，为中国区的客户提供NGS panel设计，synbio相关产品的售前售后全方位、深层次的技术支持。您不仅需要具备深厚的生命科学背景知识和一定的生物信息学知识，还需要解答产品问题，成为基础科研客户和工业客户（包含抗体开发、细胞治疗、基因治疗及AI药物开发等领域）中的可信赖顾问，通过专业的技术方案解决实际难题，提升客户满意度与忠诚度。&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;核心职责&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;NGS panel设计&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;高效完成中国区NGS panel设计需求。&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;积极参与客户对于特殊panel设计的讨论。&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;与全球设计团队保持定期良好的沟通。&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;技术咨询与支持：&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;负责处理并解答客户关于DNA合成（基因、oligo pool、突变体文库等）产品的复杂技术问询，提供专业、及时、准确的解决方案。&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;深度理解客户在抗体药物发现、细胞治疗、基因治疗&amp;nbsp;等领域的应用场景，并提供基于公司产品的研究方案。&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;客户关系管理：&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;主动跟进重点客户的研发项目，建立并维护良好的技术信任关系，提升客户满意度和产品粘性。&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;收集、分析并反馈客户需求及市场趋势，为公司的产品开发、市场策略提供决策依据。&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;跨部门协作：&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;与销售团队紧密合作，参与重要客户的技术拜访，提供专业技术演示，协助达成销售目标。&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;与研发和生产部门协同，深入调查并解决客户反馈的复杂技术问题，推动产品质量和流程的持续改进。&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;任职要求&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;教育背景：&lt;/strong&gt;&amp;nbsp;分子生物学、生物化学、细胞生物学、生物工程或相关专业硕士及以上学历。&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;工作经验：&lt;/strong&gt;&amp;nbsp;拥有3-5年及以上在知名生物科技公司、CRO或药企的研发、应用支持经验。&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;专业知识&lt;/strong&gt;：&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;熟悉linux的基本操作，有一定的生物信息学基础。&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;深刻理解寡核苷酸和基因合成技术的原理、工艺及质量控制要点。&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;熟悉DNA合成产品在以下至少两个领域的应用：&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;ol&gt;
&lt;li&gt;抗体新药开发:&amp;nbsp;如抗体库构建、人源化、亲和力成熟、序列优化。&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;细胞治疗:&amp;nbsp;如CAR结构设计、病毒载体构建、T细胞功能验证。&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;基因治疗:&amp;nbsp;如AAV基因组设计、sgRNA筛选、mRNA疫苗/LNP应用。&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;AI在药物开发中的应用。&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ol&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;实验技能：&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;具备分子生物学和细胞生物学实验操作经验，包括但不限于：分子克隆、质粒构建、PCR、细胞培养、转染/转导。&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;能够独立解决客户的技术问题。&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;沟通能力：&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;出色的中英文沟通能力（书面和口语），能够清晰、有逻辑地向不同背景的客户解释复杂技术概念。&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;卓越的客户服务意识、主动性和解决问题的能力。&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;优秀的团队协作精神和项目管理能力。&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Job Overview&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;This position requires an expert with both a profound technical background and excellent communication skills. You will serve as a crucial bridge connecting the company&#39;s products with customer success, providing comprehensive and in-depth technical support for NGS panel design and synbio-related products to customers in China, both pre-sales and post-sales. You not only need to possess deep background in life sciences and knowledge of bioinformatics, but also be able to answer product questions, act as a trusted advisor for both basic research and industrial customers (encompassing antibody development, cell therapy, gene therapy and AI driven drug discovery), and solve practical problems through professional technical solutions to enhance customer satisfaction and loyalty.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Core Responsibilities&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;NGS Panel Design&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Efficiently fulfill NGS panel design requirements in China.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Actively participate in discussions with customers regarding special panel designs.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Maintain regular and effective communication with the global design team.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Technical Consultation and Support&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Handle and

&lt;p&gt;Couldn&#39;t find a role that is a perfect fit for your background and career interests?&amp;nbsp;We&#39;ve created this general job application so you can submit your resume and get on the Recruiting Team&#39;s radar.&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Please submit a resume and cover letter, along with a way to get a hold of you in the future. A cover letter isn&#39;t necessary, but it&#39;s a nice way to give us a hint about what you want to do here at Twist.&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The Recruiting Team will review your information. If a current role fits with your interests, we&#39;ll reach out right away. If not, your information will be kept on file for future roles. Twist&amp;nbsp;Bioscience is growing and we&#39;ll likely have new positions open very soon.&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Thanks for your interest!&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p class=&quot;p1&quot;&gt;&lt;strong&gt;About Twist Bioscience&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 400;&quot;&gt;Twist Bioscience synthesizes genes from scratch, known as “writing” DNA. Just as children learn to both read and write, the next phase of development for the genomics revolution is the ability to write DNA.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 400;&quot;&gt;At Twist Bioscience, we work in service of people who are changing the world for the better. In fields such as health care, agriculture, industrial chemicals and data storage, our unique silicon-based DNA Synthesis Platform provides precision at a scale that is otherwise unavailable to our customers.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
