&lt;h2&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Manager, Antibody Characterization (onsite in Quincy, MA)&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;h3&gt;&lt;strong&gt;JOB DESCRIPTION&amp;nbsp;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;p&gt;This is a management position that provides support for bioanalytical characterization for a variety of therapeutic antibody candidates. This role oversees our Antibody Characterization team and is responsible for managing, optimizing, and troubleshooting a range of workflows, including immunoassays, affinity analysis, functional assays, and target binding characterization.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;h3&gt;&lt;strong&gt;ESSENTIAL FUNCTIONS&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Lead, manage, and develop a team of scientists and research associates in our Antibody Characterization department.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Provide technical guidance (assay development, analysis, and data reporting) in a range of areas, including high-throughput ELISA, flow cytometry, kinetic assays (BLI and SPR), advanced/custom characterization, and functional screening.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Serve as an end-to-end technical lead for a variety of &lt;em&gt;in vivo&lt;/em&gt; antibody discovery programs and contract services, contributing to scientific planning and feasibility review during project scoping.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Review, critically analyze, and present data to customers to facilitate antibody lead selection for a variety of concurrent antibody discovery programs.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Work closely with the Project Management team to communicate timelines and deliverables to internal and external stakeholders and customers.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Work closely with all scientific departments and senior management to ensure excellent management of all activities and effective communication.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Promote operational and scientific excellence by driving continuous process improvement.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Stay up to date with recent developments in antibody discovery methods and technologies, and help guide the advancement of our laboratory capabilities in alignment with strategic company goals.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Spend approximately 30-50% of your time performing wet-lab benchwork alongside the team.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;h3&gt;&lt;strong&gt;POSITION QUALIFICATIONS &lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;PhD in a related technical field with 3+ years of management experience in biopharmaceutical analytical development, or MS with 5+ years of experience, including 3+ years of management experience.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Expert knowledge of biologics characterization assays: extensive hands-on experience required in ELISA, flow cytometry, and/ or SPR/BLI with Carterra and Sartorius Octet.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Very strong track record of developing, executing, and analyzing common assay formats for biologics discovery, such as high-throughput screening, epitope binning, ligand blocking analysis, affinity analysis, and cell-based functional assays.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Able to independently manage and prioritize tasks in a fast-paced environment that hinges on overlapping projects and sensitive workflow timelines.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Advanced understanding of&amp;nbsp;&lt;em&gt;in vivo &lt;/em&gt;antibody discovery concepts.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Proven ability to assess, interpret, and present complex scientific data effectively and with a high level of integrity and ethics.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Proven management skills for both projects and people, with a strong track record of building trust and developing teams at a variety of levels.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Exceptional written and verbal communication skills, including customer-facing communication.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Highly organized and detail-oriented with a focused, problem-solving mentality to address projects and logistics.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;h2&gt;&lt;strong&gt;About Twist Bioscience&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 400;&quot;&gt;Twi

&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: 400;&quot;&gt;We are looking for motivated, enthusiastic individuals to join our Twist Bioscience Operations team in Wilsonville, OR. The Manufacturing Associate will produce various DNA and plasmid products, focusing on molecular and cellular biology, as well as running analytic techniques in the high-throughput/highly-automated lab according to established SOPs, along with working with sensitive equipment and following good manufacturing practices. Candidates must also be a team player, neat and highly organized, able to work in a cleanroom environment and foster safe work practices.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
